{
  "stem": "19923.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There had been one group that preceded us that went to the United States.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were the second group and the last group to get out under Eleanor Roosevelt's program before the United States entered the war and of course, then the rescue the children program completely ceased.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But from Marseilles, we-- we were able to board a train, all of us, and there were about 50 some in the group from various parts of Europe.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we went all the way to Lisbon through Spain.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Lisbon, we stayed there four in a villa for six weeks until finally we caught a boat.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were supposed to go on a boat first to Cuba, called the N-Y-A-S-S-A.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But for some reason, we never got that boat and we finally got a boat, a Portuguese boat, that used to be owned by Britain called S-E-R-P-A, Pinto, P-I-N-T-O.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that boat went from Lisbon to-- to Casablanca, made a stop in Casablanca, then from Casablanca went to Bermuda and finally from Bermuda went to New York.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "15 days.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was a-- it was a freight boat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, we had steerage, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was pretty uncomfortable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But who cared?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were on the way to America.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we had a couple of alarms, alerts of German torpedoes, torpedo boats being in the area.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But these things were just false alarms and we were able to make it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The-- the boat took a slow way and zigzagged in order to avoid the German U-boats and finally landed in New York on September 24, 1941.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we saw the Statue of Liberty and we all knew we were safe.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now, my mother and my sisters, going back to 1940, in May 1940, when Germany overran Belgium, they were trapped.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
